This paper deals with the problem of counting small patterns in permutations, which is a fundamental problem in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also proposes new algorithms for counting these patterns, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of these algorithms in nonparametric statistics, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational statistics (cs.CC).
